<p>As Christmas dinner wines age, tannins polymerize and soften, primary fruit flavors evolve into secondary characteristics—leather, earth, and forest floor in reds; honeyed nuts and dried fruits in aged whites. <strong>Peak drinking windows</strong> typically occur when fruit intensity balances perfectly with developed complexity: 5-8 years for quality Chianti Classico Riserva, 7-12 years for premier cru Burgundy.</p>

